               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 8 works (a-h)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous Persian works on Sufism, comprised of heterogeneous parts from differing sources. Volume not dated; individual items dated (items b, e, and h), ranging 5 Jumādá al-S̲ānī 1083-16 Rabīʿ al-Avval 1152/28 September 1672-23 June 1739. Parts date from the period of Nadir Shah Afshar’s invasion of India and occupation of Delhi. Summaries of contents on folios 1r and 161v. Awkward scribal nastaʿlīq, naskh, and shikastah āmīz hands. Stamped foliation and discontinuous earlier Persian foliation. Lacks original binding. Original text cropped, cut and remounted with new margins in gutter. Folios subsequently rebound in IOL red half leather binding, stamp dated 18 Feb 1936. Folios damaged by large wormholes, gauze net overlay throughout, later repairs, cropped margins, and occasional stains. Labels from the earlier wrapper remounted at beginning. Condition moderately fragile. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1179-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="24v">ff. 1v-24v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. 
</p>
                        <p>Collection of quatrains or rubāʿīyāt on Ṣūfī themes by Jāmī Hiravī (d. 898/1492). 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                        <p>Annotations between lines and margins. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20830">Lavāʾiḥ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20830">لوائح</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_90042997">Jāmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_90042997">جامى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1179-item2">
                     <locus from="25r" to="95v">ff. 25r-95v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. 
</p>
                        <p>Untitled excerpt from a collection of the dicta or fiqarāt ascribed to the Ṣūfī saint, <persName key="viaf_485149294387580522619" role="ant">Khvājah ʿUbayd Allāh Aḥrār</persName> (d. circa 895/1490). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 95v): completed by <persName key="person_f7027" role="scr">ʿAbd al-Raḥīm</persName> in <placeName>Shāhjahānābād</placeName>, morning of 16 Rabīʿ al-Avval in RY 21 (?) of <persName key="viaf_45680638" role="oth">Emperor Muḥammad Shāh</persName> (1152)/23 June 1739, written at the request of <persName key="person_f7317" role="pat">Miyān Ghulām Nabī</persName>, and submitted for correction to <persName key="person_f7319" role="crr">Miyān Lād Khān</persName>. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1179-item3">
                     <locus from="96r" to="99v">ff. 96r-99v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. 
</p>
                        <p>Treatise guiding aspirant novices on the Naqshbandī Ṣūfī path by Jāmī (d. 898/1492). 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_90042997" type="supplied">Jāmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_90042997" type="supplied">جامى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2858">Bayān-i ṭarīqah-'i ḥaz̤rat-i khvājagān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_2858">بيان طريقهٴ حضرت خواجگان</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1179-item4">
                     <locus from="100v" to="134r">ff. 100v-134r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. 
</p>
                        <p>Commentary by Jami (d. 898/1492) on a collection of his own quatrains or rubāʿīyāt. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7788">Sharḥ-i rubāʿīyāt-i Mullā Jāmī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_7788">شرح رباعيات ملّا جامى</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName key="viaf_90042997" type="supplied" xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Jāmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_90042997">جامى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1179-item5">
                     <locus from="134r" to="137v">ff. 134r-137v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. 
</p>
                        <p>Rare treatise collecting the dicta of <persName key="person_f1852" role="aut">Saʿd al-Dīn Kāshgharī</persName> (d. 860/1456), master or murshid of the great Ṣūfī and poet, <persName key="viaf_90042997" role="oth">Mullā Nūr al-Dīn ʿAbd al-Raḥmān Jāmī</persName> (d. 898/1492), mainly on the subject of tavajjuh or instinctive thinking toward God. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 137v): completed by <persName key="person_f7027" role="scr">ʿAbd al-Raḥīm</persName>, 28 Muḥarram in RY 17 of <persName key="viaf_45680638" role="oth">Emperor Muḥammad Shāh</persName>, (1147?)/30 June 1734. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7878">Risālah-'i Saʿd al-Dīn Kāshgharī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_7878">رسالهٴ سعد الدّين كاشغرى</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f1852">Saʿd al-Dīn Kāshgharī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f1852">سعد الدّين كاشغرى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1179-item6">
                     <locus from="138r" to="138r">f. 138r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item f. 
</p>
                        <p>Untitled note giving instructions for the performance of ablutions and elective prayers, mentioning the name of a certain <persName key="person_f7073" role="oth">Amīn Khān</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1179-item7">
                     <locus from="139r" to="145r">ff. 139r-145r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item g. 
</p>
                        <p>Brief treatise commenting on the Ṣūfī mnemotechnical phrase, <title>hūsh dar dam va khilvat dar anjuman</title>, with the aid of quotations from the <title>Qurʾān</title> and Ḥadīs̲, by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Rough shikastah āmīz and naskh. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8706">Hūsh dar dam</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_8706">هوش در دم</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1179-item8">
                     <locus from="146v" to="160r">ff. 146v-160r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item h. 
</p>
                        <p>Treatise epitomising Naqshbandī Ṣūfī doctrine by a certain Ḥusayn ibn Ibn Yamīn al-Ḥusaynī. 
Although little is known of this author, Arberry suggests he flourished in the sixteenth century. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is divided into three sections termed aṣl. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 160r): completed by <persName key="person_f7535" role="scr">Sayyid Muḥammad ʿĀdil Gardīzī Sarhindī</persName>, Thursday, 5 Jumādá al-S̲ānī 1083/28 September 1672. This is followed by a medical prescription for bleeding haemorrhoids and other conditions. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq becoming course towards the end. 
</p>
                        <p>This item is particularly damaged by prominent clusters of wormholes. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21721">Mirʾāt al-badāʾiʿ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21721">مرآة البدائع</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7170" type="supplied">Ḥusayn ibn Ibn Yamīn al-Ḥusaynī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7170" type="supplied">حسين ابن ابن يمين الحسينى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
